<item>
            <title>[FLINK-9601] Snapshot of CopyOnWriteStateTable will failed when the amount of record is more than MAXIMUM_CAPACITY</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-9601</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In short, the problem is that we reuse the `snaphotData` as the output array when partitioning the input data, but the `snapshotData` is max length is `1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 30`. So when the records in `CopyOnWriteStateTable` is more than `1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt; 30` (e.g. 1 &amp;lt;&amp;lt;30 + 1), then the check `Preconditions.checkState(partitioningDestination.length &amp;gt;= numberOfElements);` could be failed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13166526">FLINK-9601</key>
            <summary>Snapshot of CopyOnWriteStateTable will failed when the amount of record is more than MAXIMUM_CAPACITY</summary>
